  "notes": "Afar (Qafár af), Lowland East Cushitic, Djibouti/Eritrea/Ethiopia. Official Latin orthography (the 'Qafar Feera', adopted 1976) is phonemic: long vowels are written double (aa, ee, ii, oo, uu), <c> = /ħ/, <q> = /ʕ/, <x> = /ɖ/ (retroflex stop), <r> = /ɾ/. <ch>, <kh>, <sh>, <dh> occur mainly in loanwords. Tone/accent is not written.",
